727772f-a.text:
Queens Boulevard, south side, (of the old Hoffman Boulevard), between Seventieth Avenue (right) and 70th Road (left), showing John E. Backus' house. The one-story shed at the extreme right of the house does not show in the 1927 Queens Atlas. This is a set of four views. An occupant of this house was Jacob W. Zipp in 1924. 0ther owners were E. Strong, 1852; A. Whitson Est., 1860; A. Backus, 1873; and John E. Backus in 1891.
February 1923.

View 2: April 1923.
View 3: July 1923.
View 4: August 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727773f-c.text:
Queens Boulevard, south side (of the old Hoffman Boulevard) between Seventieth Avenue (right) and 70th Road (left), showing John H. Backus' house. The one-story shed at the extreme right of the house does not show in the 1927 Queens Atlas. John E. Backus, son of Ascan Backus was born in 1946 and join his ancestors in 1911. In 1873, he married Phoebe S. Vanderveer, daughter of Isaac W. Vanderveer and grand daughter of John R. Pitkin. The sons of this union were T. Eugene Backus and I Wyckoff Backus. See also other views for more data.
